<p>In <a href="/wiki/Web_development" title="Web development">web development</a>, a <b>mashup</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Web_application" title="Web application">Web application</a> that combines data from one or more sources into a single integrated tool. The term <b>Mashup</b> implies easy, fast integration, frequently done by access to open <a href="/wiki/API" title="API" class="mw-redirect">APIs</a> and data sources to produce results that were not the original reason for producing the raw source data. An example of a mashup is the use of cartographic data from <a href="/wiki/Google_Maps" title="Google Maps">Google Maps</a> to add location information to <a href="/wiki/Real_estate" title="Real estate">real estate</a> data, thereby creating a new and distinct Web service that was not originally provided by either source.</p>
